                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15253143" author="stefania" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2016 01:34:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I should add that the intention of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-11053&quot; title=&quot;COPY FROM on large datasets: fix progress report and optimize performance part 4&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-11053&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-11053&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; was for people to build the Cython extensions manually, for performance reasons only, as explained in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.datastax.com/dev/blog/six-parameters-affecting-cqlsh-copy-from-performance&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;this blog&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15253192" author="stefania" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2016 02:16:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This simple &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/stef1927/cassandra/commits/11630-2.1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;patch&lt;/a&gt; should do the trick if we need this, waiting to hear from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mshuler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mshuler&quot;&gt;mshuler&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15254751" author="mshuler" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2016 21:42:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Your patch works perfectly to suppress the cython build of copyutil and the need for the build dependency in our deb build. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15254755" author="mshuler" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2016 21:46:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pbuilder log of trunk commit 7afc157 + patch attached for fun (says 3.4, since that&apos;s what&apos;s currently in debian/changelog)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15255758" author="stefania" created="Mon, 25 Apr 2016 00:35:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for testing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mshuler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mshuler&quot;&gt;mshuler&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would you mind reviewing &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thobbs&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thobbs&quot;&gt;thobbs&lt;/a&gt;? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 2.1 patch is in the links section or mentioned a couple of comments above. I can take care of up-merging and committing if you are +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257780" author="stefania" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 09:00:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tjake&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tjake&quot;&gt;tjake&lt;/a&gt; may want to review this since he is generating the Apache packages. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The 2.1 patch applies to other branches as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15258306" author="tjake" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 15:36:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 worked for me locally&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15259281" author="stefania" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2016 00:49:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you. Committed to 2.1 as b25139f8ac5dd8a2955c4a0c13df61d529852e2f and merged upwards.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
